I've updated 2014-11-27-netbsd6-hpcarm.img.gz for hpcarm.

ftp://ftp.netbsd.org/pub/NetBSD/misc/jun/hpcarm/2014-11-27-netbsd6-hpcarm.img.gz

Feature:
- NetBSD 6.1.5-PATCH-201411220850Z hpcarm from nyftp.netbsd
- pkgsrc-current 2014-11-22 tarball from ftp.NetBSD.
- dmesg:
  https://github.com/ebijun/NetBSD/blob/master/hpcarm/Image/dmesg

Pre-compiled packages:
- Pre-compiled packages path setting: see /etc/pkg_install.conf 
PKG_PATH=http://teokurebsd.org/netbsd/packages/arm/6.1.4_2014Q1/All/
 To install application.
 # pkg_add some_application_name

 If you update pkgsrc by yourself,comment out /etc/pkg_install.conf and check
 /etc/mk.conf.

Todo:
- switch to hpcearm
  NetBSD-7.99.1-hpcarm-201411260130Z boot fine,
  but random hungs during pkgsrc build.

=====================

For OpenSourceConference 2015 Oita NetBSD booth
(https://www.facebook.com/events/383442128496493/)
demonstration use, I've updated hpcarm image.

- NetBSD 6.1.5 base
- Copy image to Mini/MicroSD.
- Set WZERO3.
- boot hpcboot.exe
-- select Machine
-- select root partition
  and comes as you are as you want to be.
- login root (no passwd)
- check symblic link:
  default:
  ls -l /etc/X11/xorg.conf -> xorg.conf.ws011sh
- startx ,and icewm running.
- running mikutter.

  # startx
  # mikutter &

Features:
  - fit size for 2GB SD Card
  - with X11
  - pkgsrc: 2014-11-22 tree inside.
  - pre-build packages
    http://teokurebsd.org/netbsd/packages/arm/6.1.4_2014Q1/All/

Installed Packages:
 https://github.com/ebijun/NetBSD/blob/master/hpcarm/Image/pkgsrc/pkginfo

kterm
tcsh
vlgothic-ttf
icewm
xli
mikutter
medit
uim
fossil
sudo
git-base
zsh
dillo
mlterm
pkg_chk
mozilla-rootcerts

Keyboard layout checkpoint:
/etc/wscons.conf
 #encoding sv
 #encoding us.swapctrlcaps
 encoding jp

/root/.xinitrc
 setxkbmap -model jp106 jp

Build sample script:
 https://github.com/ebijun/NetBSD/tree/master/hpcarm/Image

Guide:
 https://github.com/ebijun/NetBSD/blob/master/Guide/WZERO3.rst

BUGS:
 No thugs in our house.

One more time: (we're gonna celebrate

 1. login root
 2. mlterm-fb 
 3. ftp http://mlterm.sf.net/vimperator.six
 4. cat vimperator.six
 5. exit 
 6. mlterm-fb --rotate=left
 7. cat vimperator.six

